                        <h1 class="title-widget">Publications</h1>                          
                        <ul class="list-unstyled">                          
                            <li class="recent-news-wrap">                           
                                <h1 class="title-median">Publications of the Academy</h1>
                                <div class="recent-news-meta">&nbsp;</div>
                                <div class="recent-news-content clearfix">
                                    <div class="recent-news-text clear-margins">
                                        <p><img src="<?=PUBLIC_URL?>images/stock/publCover.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail img-responsive pull-left" alt="Thumbnail 1"> Among the activities undertaken by the Academy since 1934, to promote and disseminate science, publications has occupied pride of place. Indeed the first issue of the Academy’s earliest publication titled ‘Academy Proceedings’, a monthly, appeared in July 1934, the very month that the Academy was formally founded. Publication of science journals has since remained an important activity. Today the Academy publishes 10 science journals in various disciplines. Starting 2007, the Academy journals are being co-published with Springer. <a href="<?=BASE_URL?>Journals/Overview/" class="moretag" title="read more">More</a></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li><!-- widgets list end -->
                    <li class="widget-container widget_recent_news"><!-- widgets list -->               
                        <h1 class="title-widget">Chairs</h1>                         
                        <ul class="list-unstyled">                          
                            <li class="recent-news-wrap">                           
                                <h1 class="title-median">Raman Chair</h1>
                                <div class="recent-news-meta">&nbsp;</div>
                                <div class="recent-news-content clearfix">
                                    <div class="recent-news-text clear-margins">
                                        <p><img src="<?=PUBLIC_URL?>images/stock/TJ_Pedley.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail img-responsive pull-left" alt="Thumbnail 1"> The Raman Chair was instituted in 1972 by the Government of India to commemorate the memory of the founder of the Academy, Sir C. V. Raman. Eminent scientists are invited by the Council of the Academy to occupy the Chair, for periods of between six weeks and six months.  <a href="<?=BASE_URL?>About_IASc/Raman_Chair/#latest">Prof. T. J. Pedley</a>, G. I. Taylor Chair Professor, Department of Theoretical and Applied Mechanics, University of Cambridge, Cambridge (UK), has occupied the Chair on 10 February 2016.  <a href="<?=BASE_URL?>About_IASc/Raman_Chair/" class="moretag" title="read more">More</a></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="recent-news-wrap">                           
                                <h1 class="title-median">Jubilee Chair</h1>
                                <div class="recent-news-meta">&nbsp;</div>
                                <div class="recent-news-content clearfix">
                                    <div class="recent-news-text clear-margins">
                                        <p><img title="Prof. Madhu Sudan" src="<?=PUBLIC_URL?>images/stock/Madhu-Sudan.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail img-responsive pull-left" alt="Thumbnail 1">The Jubilee Professorship was instituted during the Platinum Jubilee Year of the Academy that is 2009. Eminent scientists from any country and from any scientific discipline are invited to occupy the Jubilee Professorship for a minimum period of two weeks and up to one month. <a href="<?=BASE_URL?>About_IASc/Jubilee_Chair/#occupants">Prof. Ashok R. Venkitaraman</a>, (University of Cambridge, UK), <a href="<?=BASE_URL?>About_IASc/Jubilee_Chair/#occupants">Prof. Nitash P. Balsara</a> (University of California, Berkeley, USA) and <a href="<?=BASE_URL?>About_IASc/Jubilee_Chair/#occupants">Prof. Madhu Sudan</a> (Harvard University, Cambridge, USA) have occupied the chair so far. <a href="<?=BASE_URL?>About_IASc/Jubilee_Chair/" class="moretag" title="read more">More</a></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li><!-- widgets list end -->
                    <li class="widget-container widget_recent_news"><!-- widgets list -->               
                        <h1 class="title-widget">Special Focus</h1>                         
                        <ul class="list-unstyled">                          
                            <li class="recent-news-wrap">                           
                                <h1 class="title-median">University education in science</h1>
                                <div class="recent-news-meta">&nbsp;</div>
                                <div class="recent-news-content clearfix">
                                    <div class="recent-news-text clear-margins">
                                        <p><a target="_blank" href="<?=RESOURCES_URL?>Other_Publications/Overview/postschool_science.pdf">Report</a> on brainstorming session on science academies' initiative on post-school science education (2009), held on 12 January 2009 at Indian National Science Academy, New Delhi. Restructuring post-school science teaching programmes (2008), a <a target="_blank" href="<?=RESOURCES_URL?>Other_Publications/Overview/sci_teach_pgms.pdf">'Position Paper'</a> prepared on behalf of the three national science academies of India, explaining the limitations of the present system of post-school science education in India and proposing introduction of a four-year BS programme. Higher education in science and research &amp; development: the challenges and the road ahead (2006), <a target="_blank" href="<?=RESOURCES_URL?>Other_Publications/Overview/planning_commission.pdf">recommendations</a> submitted to the Planning Commission for the 11th Five-Year Plan, prepared jointly by INSA and IAS. <a target="_blank" href="<?=BASE_URL?>Publications/Overview/report">Report</a> on university education in science (1994).</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
